Chilling photos show a blood-stained subway car with bullet holes and spent shell casings strewn about it after Tuesdayâ€™s shocking shooting aboard the train. At least 29 people were injured, 10 of them with bullet wounds, in the mayhem. Snapshots show streaks of blood marring the N train car, with items left behind by panicked straphangers or first responders during the morning rush-hour assault at a Sunset Park subway station. A backpack, laundry basket and what appears to be a police radio lay on the ground alongside several spent shell casings. Several bullet holes and shattered glass can be seen near one subway car door. Police said the gunman detonated a smoke grenade before he opened fire inside the crowded train. The NYPS has launched a massive manhunt for the gunman.